ATTACHMENT A Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 AES Laurel Mountain, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
AES LAUREL MOUNTAIN, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
AES Laurel Mountain, LLC ("Laurel Mountain") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Laurel Mountain generating facility ("Laurel Mountain Facility").
The Laurel Mountain Facility is a solar generating facility located in Barbour County, West Virginia. The Laurel Mountain Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Monongahela Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Laurel Mountain's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Laurel Mountain Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Laurel Mountain's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Laurel Mountain shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $371,773.12 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $30,981.14
